      <summary>What happens in the first meeting?</summary>
      <p>The first conversation is about fit, priorities, and whether a structured advice process makes sense for your situation. It is calm, practical, and not a hard sell.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you only work with retirees?</summary>
      <p>No. The practice is especially useful for people approaching retirement, already drawing income, supporting families, or making bigger long-term planning decisions.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can you help review my current investments or annuities?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Existing structures, withdrawals, risks, and suitability can be reviewed to see whether they still fit your goals and current circumstances.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What documents should I have ready?</summary>
      <p>Usually policy schedules, investment statements, ID, and anything that shows your current financial structure. The exact list can be confirmed before onboarding.</p>
